1
00:00:10,100 --> 00:00:11,767
<i> Mom, I'm so exhausted.</i>

2
00:00:11,900 --> 00:00:13,633
<i> I can't bear it anymore.</i>

3
00:00:13,767 --> 00:00:15,833
<i>I'm tired of forcing myself
on my dad.</i>

4
00:00:15,967 --> 00:00:17,467
<i>He never treated me
like family,</i>

5
00:00:17,600 --> 00:00:18,267
<i> so I'm going to do the same.</i>

6
00:00:18,400 --> 00:00:20,133
<i>It'll be a perfect partnership.</i>

7
00:00:20,267 --> 00:00:22,300
<i> There are no cameras here.</i>

8
00:00:22,433 --> 00:00:24,800
<i> You can do whatever you want.</i>

9
00:00:24,933 --> 00:00:26,367
<i> Can you please just get out?</i>

10
00:00:26,500 --> 00:00:29,067
<i>Marj, are you hoping your
husband's going to come</i>

11
00:00:29,200 --> 00:00:30,167
<i> pick you up?</i>

12
00:00:30,300 --> 00:00:33,600
<i>I won't force myself
where I'm not wanted.</i>

13
00:00:35,067 --> 00:00:36,200
<i> Is this really the last time?</i>

14
00:00:36,333 --> 00:00:38,967
<i> Why end something good?</i>

15
00:00:39,100 --> 00:00:40,300
<i> You're right, Mom.</i>

16
00:00:40,433 --> 00:00:43,267
<i>I hadn't even noticed that
I've been neglecting my husband.</i>

17
00:00:43,400 --> 00:00:44,433
<i> So I'm going home.</i>

18
00:00:44,567 --> 00:00:45,400
<i> I'm going to fix this.</i>

19
00:00:45,533 --> 00:00:47,200
<i> I cooked your favorite.</i>

20
00:00:47,333 --> 00:00:48,600
<i> Oscar's waiting for me.</i>

21
00:00:48,733 --> 00:00:51,500
<i>Maybe it won't just be Jasmine's
blood you need to get checked on</i>

22
00:00:51,633 --> 00:00:52,867
<i> your next hospital visit.</i>

23
00:00:53,000 --> 00:00:56,367
<i>When the body's weak,
it catches viruses easily.</i>

24
00:00:56,500 --> 00:00:58,733
<i>The same goes for relationships,
right?</i>

25
00:00:59,867 --> 00:01:00,933
What's this for?

26
00:01:02,467 --> 00:01:04,733
Just a small gesture.

27
00:01:04,867 --> 00:01:07,500
You caught me on a bad day
last time.

28
00:01:07,667 --> 00:01:11,200
I said some things
I shouldn't have.

29
00:01:12,167 --> 00:01:13,567
I'm really sorry, Evelyn.

30
00:01:16,633 --> 00:01:18,533
You didn't have to do that.

31
00:01:20,833 --> 00:01:22,367
Please, just accept it.

32
00:01:23,467 --> 00:01:26,433
Not everyone can do what you do.

33
00:01:27,367 --> 00:01:30,867
Every day, you bring and pick up
Jobert and support him.

34
00:01:31,000 --> 00:01:33,300
You'd do anything for him.

35
00:01:33,433 --> 00:01:36,200
And then there's...

36
00:01:36,333 --> 00:01:37,867
someone annoying like me.

37
00:01:40,767 --> 00:01:42,633
Consider this my peace offering.

38
00:01:42,767 --> 00:01:45,200
A show of appreciation, Evelyn.

39
00:01:47,333 --> 00:01:48,467
Please.

40
00:01:57,033 --> 00:01:58,300
I just have a meeting inside.

41
00:01:59,933 --> 00:02:01,600
Good day, Evelyn.

42
00:02:01,733 --> 00:02:02,567
Jobert?

43
00:02:04,167 --> 00:02:05,867
Bye, Uncle Greg.

44
00:02:14,367 --> 00:02:15,300
Thank you.

45
00:02:27,400 --> 00:02:31,900
Mom, you look even prettier
when you smile.

46
00:02:32,800 --> 00:02:37,467
You just lit up when Uncle Greg
gave you the gift.

47
00:02:40,900 --> 00:02:42,767
So pretty, Mom.

48
00:03:50,100 --> 00:03:51,233
Manang...

49
00:03:53,533 --> 00:03:54,533
Why?

50
00:03:56,233 --> 00:03:58,033
This is my salary.

51
00:03:58,167 --> 00:03:59,167
It's all here.

52
00:04:05,167 --> 00:04:06,800
Why are you giving that to me?

53
00:04:11,167 --> 00:04:16,233
It's to help cover
the money you lost.

54
00:04:16,367 --> 00:04:18,867
Cheche, no.

55
00:04:28,567 --> 00:04:30,400
But, Manang, it was my fault.

56
00:04:34,500 --> 00:04:36,833
I was the one
who took you there.

57
00:04:39,333 --> 00:04:45,067
We wouldn't have gone there
if it weren't for me.

58
00:04:45,200 --> 00:04:46,367
It already happened.

59
00:04:47,867 --> 00:04:49,100
There's nothing we can do.

60
00:04:51,767 --> 00:04:53,333
Just forget about it.

61
00:04:53,467 --> 00:04:54,733
But, Manang.

62
00:05:03,667 --> 00:05:05,133
So? Was it a success?

63
00:05:08,200 --> 00:05:09,467
She didn't want to accept it.

64
00:05:14,200 --> 00:05:15,233
She said it's fine.

65
00:05:18,433 --> 00:05:21,433
But I feel like she just said
that through gritted teeth.

66
00:05:21,567 --> 00:05:23,167
She still seems upset.

67
00:05:33,067 --> 00:05:34,133
Hi, love.

68
00:05:39,367 --> 00:05:41,767
Looks like you had
a stressful day.

69
00:05:41,900 --> 00:05:42,733
Yeah.

70
00:05:43,367 --> 00:05:45,633
We're still having a hard time
moving the units

71
00:05:45,767 --> 00:05:47,200
at Menagerie Manor.

72
00:05:51,167 --> 00:05:52,533
You know what, just relax.

73
00:05:53,600 --> 00:05:59,667
Let me make it up to you
for our fight last time.

74
00:07:52,933 --> 00:07:54,000
Paolo!

75
00:07:54,133 --> 00:07:55,067
Paolo!

76
00:07:55,200 --> 00:07:56,033
Paolo, wait!

77
00:07:56,167 --> 00:07:57,100
Paolo!

78
00:07:58,867 --> 00:07:59,733
What?

79
00:07:59,867 --> 00:08:01,467
What are you doing?

80
00:08:02,233 --> 00:08:03,133
What are you talking about?

81
00:08:05,167 --> 00:08:06,267
You're like a different person.

82
00:08:06,400 --> 00:08:08,467
You're hurting me.

83
00:08:08,600 --> 00:08:10,133
It's like you're somewhere else.

84
00:08:11,567 --> 00:08:13,367
What's going on with you?

85
00:08:15,833 --> 00:08:16,767
Just go to sleep.

86
00:08:53,900 --> 00:08:56,400
I'm really thrown off, girl.

87
00:08:56,533 --> 00:09:01,167
That's not something Paolo
would normally do.

88
00:09:01,300 --> 00:09:04,667
<i>Maybe your husband just wants
to try something new?</i>

89
00:09:04,800 --> 00:09:06,600
<i> Spice up your marriage.</i>

90
00:09:06,733 --> 00:09:08,867
<i>Especially since things
have been a little rocky.</i>

91
00:09:10,200 --> 00:09:11,267
Maybe.

92
00:09:14,067 --> 00:09:15,600
Let's talk later.

93
00:09:15,733 --> 00:09:18,900
I need to find Jasmine's
pill organizer.

94
00:09:19,033 --> 00:09:20,600
I think I left it in the garden.

95
00:09:23,267 --> 00:09:24,400
Okay, I'll call you again.

96
00:09:39,067 --> 00:09:43,667
I miss your hugs and kisses.

97
00:09:43,800 --> 00:09:46,967
When can I have a taste of you
again?

98
00:09:56,500 --> 00:09:57,867
What are you doing?

99
00:10:05,733 --> 00:10:07,033
Why are you hiding that?

100
00:10:08,467 --> 00:10:09,833
I'm not hiding anything.

101
00:10:11,833 --> 00:10:13,600
Don't play games with me.

102
00:10:13,733 --> 00:10:15,000
What do you call that?

103
00:10:19,167 --> 00:10:19,833
A phone.

104
00:10:21,000 --> 00:10:23,067
Why are you even snooping
through my phone?

105
00:10:25,767 --> 00:10:26,800
You're right.

106
00:10:26,933 --> 00:10:28,900
Sorry, it's none of my business.

107
00:10:30,167 --> 00:10:32,667
But I wouldn't be curious

108
00:10:32,800 --> 00:10:35,767
if you didn't overreact
when I showed up.

109
00:10:36,800 --> 00:10:38,467
It feels like you're hiding
something

110
00:10:38,600 --> 00:10:39,900
you don't want me to see.

111
00:10:41,233 --> 00:10:42,333
Oh, fine. You can have it.

112
00:10:42,467 --> 00:10:44,433
Here, look.

113
00:10:44,567 --> 00:10:46,367
I'm not hiding anything.

114
00:10:46,500 --> 00:10:47,533
So stop making things up.

115
00:10:47,667 --> 00:10:49,100
You sound crazy.

116
00:10:54,733 --> 00:10:56,767
I'm just asking.

117
00:10:56,900 --> 00:10:58,400
There's no need to get upset.

118
00:11:00,067 --> 00:11:01,867
I was just minding my own
business here,

119
00:11:02,000 --> 00:11:03,633
then you suddenly barged in.

120
00:11:04,167 --> 00:11:06,133
You know what, Marj?

121
00:11:06,267 --> 00:11:07,800
Don't take it out on me
if you're miserable

122
00:11:07,967 --> 00:11:09,800
because your kid's sick

123
00:11:09,933 --> 00:11:11,267
and your husband's going cold
on you.

124
00:11:16,133 --> 00:11:17,767
Why are you backing off?

125
00:11:17,900 --> 00:11:21,000
You talk tough,
but you're actually a coward.

126
00:11:44,400 --> 00:11:46,833
<i> So, what's the game plan?</i>

127
00:11:46,967 --> 00:11:48,333
<i> What do I need to do?</i>

128
00:11:48,467 --> 00:11:49,167
<i> Simple.</i>

129
00:11:49,300 --> 00:11:51,200
<i> I just want access.</i>

130
00:11:51,333 --> 00:11:52,333
<i> What do you mean?</i>

131
00:11:52,467 --> 00:11:55,033
<i>I want to stay one step
ahead of your brother.</i>

132
00:11:56,233 --> 00:12:01,200
<i>And to do that, I need to know
all his plans.</i>

133
00:12:01,333 --> 00:12:03,433
<i>And since you live
under the same roof,</i>

134
00:12:04,300 --> 00:12:06,000
<i> you have access to his things.</i>

135
00:12:07,133 --> 00:12:10,400
<i>Specifically,
his personal computer.</i>

136
00:12:10,533 --> 00:12:12,300
<i>So you want me to spy on Paolo?</i>

137
00:12:20,933 --> 00:12:22,533
Hello? Why are you calling?

138
00:12:23,733 --> 00:12:25,200
Yeah, I'm just at home.

139
00:12:25,333 --> 00:12:26,967
The documents?

140
00:12:27,100 --> 00:12:28,967
Yeah, I just left them
in my car.

141
00:12:31,867 --> 00:12:33,433
Yeah, they're already signed.

142
00:12:33,567 --> 00:12:36,267
Just submit them to Mr. Santos.

143
00:13:17,767 --> 00:13:18,667
Edward?

144
00:13:20,333 --> 00:13:21,700
Marj?

145
00:13:21,867 --> 00:13:23,233
What are you doing here?

146
00:13:34,700 --> 00:13:36,300
I wanted to talk to Paolo.

147
00:13:37,400 --> 00:13:38,833
But he stepped out.

148
00:13:38,967 --> 00:13:40,500
He's on the phone.

149
00:13:40,633 --> 00:13:42,767
Looks busy with work.

150
00:13:42,900 --> 00:13:45,767
So, I'll just wait for him here.

151
00:13:52,800 --> 00:13:53,633
Marj...

152
00:13:56,533 --> 00:13:58,267
Why do you look sad?

153
00:13:59,933 --> 00:14:01,467
I thought things were okay
between you and Paolo?

154
00:14:05,000 --> 00:14:06,367
We already made up.

155
00:14:06,500 --> 00:14:07,600
But...

156
00:14:09,800 --> 00:14:12,133
things still aren't back
to normal.

157
00:14:13,467 --> 00:14:14,700
I'm sorry to hear that.

158
00:14:16,000 --> 00:14:18,067
Sorry, too. I ended up venting
to you.

159
00:14:19,400 --> 00:14:21,933
I just don't have anyone else
to talk to in this house.

160
00:14:25,933 --> 00:14:28,767
Right when Jasmine
needs both of us...

161
00:14:30,467 --> 00:14:34,767
that's when we're drifting
apart.

162
00:14:39,467 --> 00:14:40,567
Marj, maybe...

163
00:14:41,867 --> 00:14:43,600
maybe Pao's just busy with work.

164
00:14:51,367 --> 00:14:52,400
I hope so.

165
00:14:52,533 --> 00:14:53,333
I really do.

166
00:14:54,200 --> 00:14:57,467
I hope he fixes whatever's
going on with his company

167
00:14:57,600 --> 00:14:59,600
so we can fix things between us,
too.

168
00:15:08,567 --> 00:15:11,067
What I asked you to do
was simple, Edward.

169
00:15:13,533 --> 00:15:15,500
So why is nothing happening?

170
00:15:17,733 --> 00:15:18,667
It's not that easy.

171
00:15:20,033 --> 00:15:21,733
What you're asking me
to do isn't simple.

172
00:15:26,167 --> 00:15:27,800
Fine.

173
00:15:27,933 --> 00:15:30,633
But make sure you bring me
good news the next time we meet.

174
00:15:32,000 --> 00:15:32,967
Okay?

175
00:15:59,900 --> 00:16:01,067
Edward?

176
00:16:02,533 --> 00:16:04,100
- Hi!
- Lalaine.

177
00:16:04,233 --> 00:16:05,667
What are you doing here?

178
00:16:08,067 --> 00:16:09,333
Just a meeting with a friend.

179
00:16:10,800 --> 00:16:12,067
You?

180
00:16:12,200 --> 00:16:12,967
Same...

181
00:16:13,100 --> 00:16:15,100
but more than a friend.

182
00:16:28,900 --> 00:16:30,000
Are you okay?

183
00:16:32,867 --> 00:16:35,133
The supplier called me again
earlier.

184
00:16:36,133 --> 00:16:37,200
They're asking for payment.

185
00:16:38,533 --> 00:16:43,067
The problem is, the company
still can't pay them.

186
00:16:44,100 --> 00:16:47,200
Because we still don't
have any revenue coming in.

187
00:16:47,333 --> 00:16:49,267
Since this project's been stuck.

188
00:16:49,400 --> 00:16:51,333
All right, I should go.

189
00:16:51,467 --> 00:16:54,500
My date might get the
wrong idea about you.

190
00:16:54,633 --> 00:16:58,467
But wait, tell your wife
to get in touch with me, okay?

191
00:16:58,600 --> 00:17:00,367
It feels like she's avoiding me.

192
00:17:00,500 --> 00:17:01,833
So crazy.

193
00:17:01,967 --> 00:17:03,133
Sure, I'll tell her.

194
00:17:04,933 --> 00:17:05,900
See you around.

195
00:17:19,233 --> 00:17:20,600
Relax, Paolo.

196
00:17:21,633 --> 00:17:23,033
We'll find a way.

197
00:17:33,333 --> 00:17:34,433
It's Edward.

198
00:17:36,800 --> 00:17:37,667
Hello?

199
00:17:38,733 --> 00:17:39,933
Hon, where are you?

200
00:17:42,433 --> 00:17:43,767
I'm with...

201
00:17:43,900 --> 00:17:44,833
Lalaine.

202
00:17:44,967 --> 00:17:46,967
Lalaine and the girls.

203
00:17:47,100 --> 00:17:48,867
What?

204
00:17:49,033 --> 00:17:50,000
You sure?

205
00:17:52,100 --> 00:17:53,200
Yeah.

206
00:18:01,933 --> 00:18:03,200
<i>Why do you sound out of breath?</i>

207
00:18:03,333 --> 00:18:04,933
Where are you?

208
00:18:05,067 --> 00:18:07,367
I told you, I'm with Lalaine.

209
00:18:07,500 --> 00:18:10,433
<i> We're at the spa.</i>

210
00:18:10,567 --> 00:18:11,400
<i>What is it with you?
Why ask if you're not going</i>

211
00:18:11,533 --> 00:18:14,400
<i> to believe me anyway?</i>

212
00:18:14,533 --> 00:18:16,067
How are you at a spa when...

213
00:18:16,200 --> 00:18:19,733
<i>You know what,
can we talk later?</i>

214
00:18:19,867 --> 00:18:21,233
<i>Aren't I supposed
to be relaxing?</i>

215
00:18:21,400 --> 00:18:23,267
You're just stressing me out.

216
00:18:23,400 --> 00:18:24,333
Bye.

217
00:18:45,367 --> 00:18:46,300
Love?

218
00:18:54,100 --> 00:18:54,933
Are you hungry?

219
00:18:55,100 --> 00:18:56,667
Yolly and I cooked for you.

220
00:18:56,800 --> 00:18:58,267
Want me to reheat it?

221
00:18:58,400 --> 00:18:59,500
No, it's fine.
I already ate at work.

222
00:19:01,400 --> 00:19:06,300
By the way, love, our supplier
friend called me.

223
00:19:06,433 --> 00:19:09,100
He's following up
on the payments.

224
00:19:09,233 --> 00:19:10,667
He said he can't get a hold
of you.

225
00:19:17,433 --> 00:19:18,533
I'll take care of it.

226
00:19:20,567 --> 00:19:23,233
Once the properties are sold,
they'll get paid.

227
00:19:25,233 --> 00:19:27,367
Is it really that bad?

228
00:19:28,267 --> 00:19:29,800
Why don't you talk to Dad?

229
00:19:29,933 --> 00:19:32,067
Maybe he can help.

230
00:19:32,200 --> 00:19:33,567
No.

231
00:19:33,700 --> 00:19:34,500
I've got this.

232
00:19:39,667 --> 00:19:41,500
Where were you earlier?

233
00:19:41,633 --> 00:19:43,567
Why do you keep asking
the same question?

234
00:19:43,700 --> 00:19:45,400
I already answered that,
didn't I?

235
00:19:45,533 --> 00:19:47,300
I went out.

236
00:19:50,267 --> 00:19:52,133
Where exactly?

237
00:19:52,267 --> 00:19:55,200
Didn't I say Lalaine
and I went to a spa?

238
00:19:55,333 --> 00:19:57,867
What is this?
An interrogation room now?

239
00:19:58,000 --> 00:19:59,967
That's impossible.

240
00:20:00,100 --> 00:20:01,167
I saw Lalaine.

241
00:20:04,167 --> 00:20:05,667
While I was on the phone
with you earlier,

242
00:20:05,800 --> 00:20:09,833
I saw her on a date at the
restaurant where I was.

243
00:20:09,967 --> 00:20:12,100
So how were you two
together at a spa?

244
00:20:13,133 --> 00:20:15,633
But doesn't Dad have connections
at the bank?

245
00:20:15,767 --> 00:20:19,533
Maybe we can get a bridge loan
to pay the suppliers?

246
00:20:20,167 --> 00:20:22,733
I said I'll handle it!

247
00:20:22,867 --> 00:20:24,000
Don't you trust me?

248
00:20:26,167 --> 00:20:27,800
Love, it's not like that.

249
00:20:27,933 --> 00:20:30,500
Then don't push it.

250
00:20:30,633 --> 00:20:32,933
Dad's already breathing down
my neck!

251
00:20:33,067 --> 00:20:34,733
And I don't want him to lose
confidence in me even more,

252
00:20:34,900 --> 00:20:35,767
so please!

253
00:20:36,833 --> 00:20:38,933
Just let me handle
this on my own!

254
00:20:59,433 --> 00:21:03,100
Edward, do you really
need to know everything?

255
00:21:03,233 --> 00:21:05,267
I'm tired.

256
00:21:05,400 --> 00:21:08,367
I don't have the energy
for your paranoia.

257
00:21:11,733 --> 00:21:13,100
What are you doing?

258
00:21:13,233 --> 00:21:14,667
Where were you, huh?

259
00:21:14,800 --> 00:21:16,300
- What are you doing?
- Where were you?

260
00:21:16,433 --> 00:21:18,667
Thea, I don't get it.

261
00:21:18,800 --> 00:21:20,900
Why do you have to lie to me?

262
00:21:21,033 --> 00:21:22,433
Are you hiding something?

263
00:21:22,567 --> 00:21:24,033
I'm not hiding anything!

264
00:21:24,167 --> 00:21:26,300
You're hurting me!

265
00:21:26,433 --> 00:21:27,500
If you're not hiding anything,

266
00:21:27,633 --> 00:21:29,333
then why can't you give me
a straight answer?

267
00:21:30,200 --> 00:21:31,333
Where were you?

268
00:21:31,467 --> 00:21:32,533
Who were you with?

269
00:21:42,433 --> 00:21:43,833
What's wrong with you, Edward?

270
00:21:46,600 --> 00:21:48,767
Okay, here's the thing.

271
00:21:48,900 --> 00:21:52,800
I was the first one to get
to the spa when you called.

272
00:21:52,933 --> 00:21:57,133
I honestly thought Lalaine
was just in the next room.

273
00:21:57,267 --> 00:21:59,367
Then I left.

274
00:21:59,500 --> 00:22:01,367
We didn't even see each other.

275
00:22:01,500 --> 00:22:05,300
But now that you've told me,
I guess I was wrong.

276
00:22:06,833 --> 00:22:09,667
So how am I supposed to know
if you're lying to me

277
00:22:09,800 --> 00:22:11,267
or just making excuses?

278
00:22:13,800 --> 00:22:15,933
Are you calling me a liar?

279
00:22:17,067 --> 00:22:17,967
Why?

280
00:22:18,100 --> 00:22:20,800
Do I need to report
my every move to you?

281
00:22:22,600 --> 00:22:23,367
Wait.

282
00:22:24,633 --> 00:22:26,833
You leave all the time, too,
right?

283
00:22:27,700 --> 00:22:30,900
You think I don't notice?

284
00:22:31,033 --> 00:22:35,300
You always have meetings,
dinners,

285
00:22:35,433 --> 00:22:37,300
you're always going out.

286
00:22:37,433 --> 00:22:39,567
And it's never clear where.

287
00:22:40,500 --> 00:22:43,200
Who are you really meeting,
Edward?

288
00:22:47,167 --> 00:22:48,300
Didn't I tell you?

289
00:22:49,733 --> 00:22:51,000
I have consultancy work.

290
00:22:53,233 --> 00:22:54,733
Oh, really?

291
00:22:55,200 --> 00:22:58,533
Then why can't you
even look me in the eye?

292
00:22:58,667 --> 00:23:01,333
Do you want me to start
asking you

293
00:23:01,467 --> 00:23:05,233
for a full report every time you
step out of this house?

294
00:23:07,733 --> 00:23:08,533
See?

295
00:23:09,800 --> 00:23:13,033
Looks like you're the one
hiding something, Edward.

296
00:23:13,633 --> 00:23:14,733
You're being unfair.

297
00:23:16,300 --> 00:23:18,067
Don't point your finger at me!

298
00:23:18,200 --> 00:23:21,533
It's not fair that you keep
accusing me out of nowhere!

299
00:23:22,200 --> 00:23:25,600
If you don't trust me,
just say it.

300
00:23:26,367 --> 00:23:31,067
Don't treat me like
I'm some house for inspection!

301
00:23:44,033 --> 00:23:46,467
Jobert, go straight ahead, okay?

302
00:23:46,600 --> 00:23:49,467
And be careful with your soup.

303
00:23:49,600 --> 00:23:50,833
You might spill it.

304
00:23:50,967 --> 00:23:52,900
Got it, Mom.
I've got it memorized.

305
00:23:53,033 --> 00:23:54,867
Memorized? Very good.

306
00:23:55,000 --> 00:23:56,300
Thanks, Mom.

307
00:23:58,067 --> 00:23:59,267
Good boy!

308
00:24:05,400 --> 00:24:06,200
Evelyn!

309
00:24:09,167 --> 00:24:10,900
What are you doing here?

310
00:24:12,467 --> 00:24:15,467
Well, every time I come
courting you at your house,

311
00:24:15,600 --> 00:24:16,833
you won't even come out.

312
00:24:16,967 --> 00:24:18,567
So I followed you here!

313
00:24:19,800 --> 00:24:22,733
Vergel, how many times
do I have to tell you?

314
00:24:22,867 --> 00:24:25,300
I'm not interested in you!

315
00:24:25,433 --> 00:24:28,533
Can you please find
someone else to bother?

316
00:24:28,700 --> 00:24:30,567
You're not getting anything
from me!

317
00:24:30,700 --> 00:24:31,800
Now, please leave!

318
00:24:31,933 --> 00:24:33,500
- Leave me alone!
- Is there a problem here?

319
00:24:33,633 --> 00:24:35,267
- Hey, hey, hey!
- You're hurting me!

320
00:24:35,400 --> 00:24:36,033
-You've got a lot of nerve, huh?
-Hey, hey, hey!

321
00:24:36,167 --> 00:24:37,867
Who you got, huh?

322
00:24:38,000 --> 00:24:39,400
Ouch!

323
00:24:39,533 --> 00:24:40,300
Let her go.

324
00:24:40,433 --> 00:24:42,067
Is he the one you are with?

325
00:24:45,567 --> 00:24:48,500
Do you want me to have you
dragged to the police station

326
00:24:48,633 --> 00:24:50,433
by the guards?

327
00:24:50,567 --> 00:24:53,000
Evelyn, we're not done yet!

328
00:24:53,133 --> 00:24:55,467
I'll be the one to tell you.

329
00:24:55,600 --> 00:24:58,100
It's done.

330
00:24:58,233 --> 00:25:00,133
The next time you bother her,

331
00:25:00,267 --> 00:25:04,000
I'll use all my connections
to hunt you down.

332
00:25:05,133 --> 00:25:09,167
I'll make sure you regret it
if you ever do anything to her.

333
00:25:09,300 --> 00:25:11,100
Now go!

334
00:25:12,267 --> 00:25:13,467
- Go!
- Get out of here!

335
00:25:13,600 --> 00:25:15,267
We're not done!

336
00:25:15,400 --> 00:25:16,633
We're not done!

337
00:25:27,833 --> 00:25:28,700
Are you okay?

338
00:25:38,733 --> 00:25:41,033
Paolo, did I do something wrong?

339
00:25:41,167 --> 00:25:43,167
If something happened,
just tell me.

340
00:25:43,300 --> 00:25:45,067
It's just that you
won't talk to me.

341
00:25:45,200 --> 00:25:47,267
Is there something
you're not telling me?

342
00:25:47,400 --> 00:25:49,767
It should be clear to you
what we are.

343
00:25:49,900 --> 00:25:51,200
And you're not my BFF.

344
00:25:51,333 --> 00:25:53,467
So don't expect me to share
my personal problems with you.

345
00:25:53,600 --> 00:25:54,967
What we have...

346
00:25:55,100 --> 00:25:56,500
work stays in the office,

347
00:25:56,633 --> 00:25:58,800
and everything else stays
in bed.

348
00:25:58,933 --> 00:26:02,133
You know, men like Paolo
and his father don't say

349
00:26:02,267 --> 00:26:04,967
when they're pulling away.

350
00:26:05,100 --> 00:26:08,033
When they don't get the
attention they want

351
00:26:08,167 --> 00:26:09,867
from their wives,

352
00:26:10,033 --> 00:26:13,000
that's when they start looking
elsewhere.

353
00:26:13,133 --> 00:26:15,533
You wouldn't want to wake up
one day

354
00:26:15,667 --> 00:26:18,200
and realize your husband
no longer loves you

355
00:26:18,333 --> 00:26:21,167
and is looking for that love
somewhere else.

356
00:26:21,300 --> 00:26:23,067
Where's Paolo?

357
00:26:23,200 --> 00:26:25,300
He's probably upstairs.

358
00:26:25,433 --> 00:26:29,600
A Torrecampo wife knows
how to keep a marriage intact.

359
00:26:29,733 --> 00:26:33,267
With grace, with effort,
with presence.

360
00:26:33,400 --> 00:26:35,567
Even if it hurts,
even if it's hard,

361
00:26:35,700 --> 00:26:37,667
act like a Torrecampo woman.
